    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n7659" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πλάζω</span></b>  (cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πλήσσω</span>), aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πλάγξε</span>, mid. fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πλάγξομαι</span>, pass. aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πλάγχθη</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πλαγχθείς</span>:
          I. act., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">strike</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            21.269</span></i>; esp., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">strike</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">drive back,
            cause to drift;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥόον, τινὰ ἀπὸ πατρίδος,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 17.751</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> α
            75</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 24.307</span></i>; met., of
          the mind, ‘make to wander,’ ‘confuse,’ <i><span class="en">Od.
            2.396</span></i>.— II. mid. and pass., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be driven, drift,
            wander;</span> ‘be struck away,’ ‘rebound,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 11.351</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
